The paper discusses the evasion of classifiers, which is a common topic in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The use of convex-inducing classifiers suggests a focus on optimization and convex optimization, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses algorithms and queries, which are common topics in computer science theory, suggesting a possible fit for cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The mention of decision boundaries and undetected instances suggests a possible fit for cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
